    "en": {
      "title": "\u2018Kovid 19\u2019 has changed: not over",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Health Organization (WHO) warns that the 'Kovid 19' corona epidemic is changing but not over yet. The World Health Organization (WHO) has warned that there is an increase in the number of Kovid 19 cases in many countries.",
        "\u2018The epidemic is changing. But not over. It is clear that there was a sharp decline in the virus. That is, with the advent of the omicchron mutation. However, subtypes of omicron mutation should be considered. Kovid 19 Immunization programs around the world have also helped to control the epidemic. Today, there is an increase of 19 cases of Covid in 19 countries. '",
        "The head of the World Health Organization explained this at a press conference in Geneva. The United Nations Headquarters is located in Geneva, Switzerland.",
        "The head of the World Health Organization (WHO) told the media that 70 percent of the world's population has now received the required dose of the Kovid 19 vaccine. In the last 18 months, 12 billion vaccines have been delivered worldwide.",
        "'BA5' and 'BA4' are the most commonly identified subtypes of the 'Kovid 19 Omicron' mutation, and the fastest-growing of these two subtypes is the 'BA5' variant. There are. It is said that the 'BA5' variant has now spread to 63 countries."
      ],
